## Documentation Quality Checklist

### Code Documentation
- [ ] All public APIs have JSDoc comments
- [ ] Examples are runnable and tested
- [ ] Error conditions are documented
- [ ] Breaking changes are versioned and documented

### Project Documentation
- [ ] README includes setup, usage, and API reference
- [ ] Environment variables are documented
- [ ] Nx targets are listed and described
- [ ] Architecture diagrams exist for complex systems

### Process Documentation
- [ ] ADRs exist for major decisions
- [ ] Development workflow is documented
- [ ] Deployment process is clear
- [ ] Troubleshooting guides exist

### Maintenance
- [ ] Documentation is reviewed in PRs
- [ ] Outdated docs are updated with code changes
- [ ] CI validates documentation generation
- [ ] Documentation is versioned with releases

## Success Metrics

- **Documentation Coverage**: > 90% of public APIs documented
- **README Completeness**: All projects have comprehensive READMEs
- **ADR Compliance**: Major decisions have corresponding ADRs
- **Documentation Freshness**: < 30 days since last update
- **Developer Satisfaction**: > 80% of developers can find needed information